**1.4** No Invented Interfaces. Verify against actual source files.

### Category 2 — Type Safety
**2.1** No ID Confusion. Key dicts by `entity.id` (global), never `entity.iid` (project-internal).
**2.2** No Untyped Containers. `dict[int, Issue]` not `dict`. `list[EntityRelationship]` not `list`.
**2.3** No `Any` Escape Hatch. `Any` only for raw JSON from `fetch_all_project_data()` return.

### Category 3 — Test Quality
**3.1** No Tautological Tests. `assert len(state.issues) == 3` not `assert state.issues`.
**3.2** No Happy-Path-Only Tests. At least 1 error/edge case per 2 happy-path tests.
**3.3** No Real API Calls. Mock `GitLabFetcher` via `unittest.mock.AsyncMock`.
**3.4** No `Contributor.updated_at` Access. This field does not exist.

### Category 4 — Async Discipline
**4.1** No Missing Awaits. Every `store.store_state()`, `store.update_entity()`, `manager.refresh_project()`, `manager.apply_webhook_event()` must be awaited.
**4.2** No Lock Bypass. Every write to `_states[project_id]` inside acquired per-project lock.
**4.3** No Sync Calls in Async Context.

### Category 5 — Naming and Consistency
**5.1** Apply canonical terminology table. Every synonym is a defect.
**5.2** `snake_case` past tense for log events: `state_refresh_completed`, `entity_updated`, `stale_event_discarded`.

### Category 6 — State Integrity
**6.1** No Unguarded State Writes. Always acquire per-project lock.
**6.2** No Input Mutation. Create new instances; never mutate Phase 0 models.
**6.3** No Completeness Upgrade via Webhook. Webhooks never set `StateCompleteness.FULL`.

### Category 7 — Spec Compliance
**7.1** `# ASSUMPTION:` prefix for any interpretation. Grep-able.
**7.2** No Forward References. Step N uses only Steps 1..N-1 and Phase 0/1 artifacts.
**7.3** No Gratuitous Abstraction.

### Category 8 — Defensive Coding
**8.1** `if value is not None:` not `if value:`.
**8.2** `state.issues.get(issue_id)` not `state.issues[issue_id]` when key may not exist.
**8.3** `isinstance(result, FetchResult)` before accessing `.items`.

### Category 9 — Context and Memory
**9.1** Re-read Invariants, step spec, and imported module interfaces from files before coding.
**9.2** Verify exact names from source files, not memory.

### Category 10 — Regression Prevention
**10.1** Read entire function before modifying.
**10.2** `grep -r "function_name" src/ tests/` before changing any signature.
**10.3** Zero test failures tolerated across all phases.

### Category 11 — Import Hygiene
**11.1** No circular imports. Follow ownership boundary directions.
**11.2** No wrong-direction dependencies. Invariant 4 enforced.
**11.3** No unused imports.

### Category 12 — Log Level Semantics

| Level | Use When |
|---|---|
| `DEBUG` | Stale event discarded, lock acquired, cache details |
| `INFO` | Refresh started/completed (with counts), container registration, entity updated |
| `WARNING` | Partial completeness set, orphaned reference, missing fetch result key |
| `ERROR` | Entity normalization failed, webhook mapping failed, project refresh failed |
| `CRITICAL` | Container state corruption, Invariant 4 violation at runtime |

### Category 13 — Temporal Coupling
**13.1** Container manages init order. `StateManager` unusable before container initialized.
**13.2** All `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` at call time, never import time.

### Category 14 — Dead Code
**14.1** No dead code. Every function called, every variable read.
**14.2** Defend external inputs. Trust type system for internal contracts.

### Category 15 — Dataclass Discipline
**15.1** Every `list`/`dict` field uses `field(default_factory=...)`. Never `= []` or `= {}`.
**15.2** No `frozen=True` on Phase 2 state models. State must be updatable.

### Category 16 — Exception Chain Discipline
**16.1** Always `raise X from e`. Never lose the traceback.
**16.2** No bare `except`. Specific types only. `except Exception` only at gather boundaries.

### Category 17 — Test Isolation
**17.1** Fresh `ProjectStateStore` instance per test via fixture.
**17.2** Every test passes when run alone.
**17.3** No time-dependent tests.

### Category 18 — Memory Bounds
**18.1** Store holds all tracked projects for container lifetime. Shutdown clears all.
**18.2** Phase 2 stores current entity state only. No history accumulation — that is Phase 3.

### Category 19 — Container Integration
**19.1** `StateManager`, `ProjectStateStore` etc. instantiated only inside `container.initialize()`.
**19.2** Post-shutdown access raises `RuntimeError`.

### Category 20 — Python Version
**20.1** Python 3.11+ only. No `type` statement (3.12+). Use `TypeAlias`.

