## What Comes Next

After Phase 2 is complete, Phase 3 (Time-Series Engine) begins. Phase 3 will:

- Read entity state from `ProjectStateStore` via `Container.get_state_store()` exclusively — never from Phase 1 fetchers directly (Invariant 1 enforced)
- Subscribe to `UpdateResult` events from `StateManager.apply_webhook_event()` to track state transitions in real time
- Record state change history: issue transitions (OPEN → CLOSED), MR lifecycle (OPEN → MERGED), pipeline outcomes (RUNNING → SUCCESS/FAILED)
- Use `IngestSummary.entities_loaded` counts over time to compute throughput metrics
- Build velocity timeseries: issues closed per day, MRs merged per sprint, pipeline success rate
- Detect trajectory changes: is velocity accelerating or decelerating? Is pipeline failure rate trending up?
- Require Phase 2 state to have `StateCompleteness.FULL` or `PARTIAL` (never `EMPTY`) before trusting as a data point
- Use `StateMetadata.last_refresh_at` as the timestamp anchor for each state snapshot

Every decision made in Phase 2 directly enables Phase 3. A well-structured, consistently complete, relationship-indexed state is the foundation of all temporal and predictive intelligence.
